close_reason: Settings and machine/user-facing contract surfaces now expose and persist init agent guidance behavior with focused regression coverage.
body: "Implementation direction:\n- Extend PmSettings with agent_guidance state and defaults in src/types.ts and src/core/shared/constants.ts.\n- Extend settings schema, merge, and serialize ordering in src/core/store/settings.ts; keep output deterministic.\n- Add init option wiring in src/cli/register-setup.ts and action schema optional keys in src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts.\n- Update help text in src/cli/help-content.ts and JSON/help payload expectations so agents discover the later-add path.\n- Consider a read/reset config key only if implementation needs an operator escape hatch beyond pm init --agent-guidance add/skip/status. If added, keep scope project-only and document clear behavior.\n- Keep MCP pm_run init schema in sync through SDK contracts so connected agents can request guidance add/status without shell-specific assumptions."
